      <TR>
        <TD bgcolor='black' valign='top'
 nowrap><b><font color='white' face='Verdana' size='2'>lorkast</font></b></td>
        <TD bgcolor='black' valign='top'><font color='white' face='Verdana' size='2'> Just did the quest and it took me about 1 hour from start to end, but I had to make a new character (Rallos Zek worshipping Troll War) to do some of the hand ins since I am KOS to giants.</P><P>I found this very nice info on how to do this quest depending on your faction on allakhazam:</P><P><i>Ok, there are 2 ways of doing this quest, depending on whether you're KOS in kael or not. For both you'll need to be at least level 50 to attempt this solo. </P><P>Method 1 (KOS) </P><P>Make a new character, a warrior (any race) with a religion of rallos zek. Get him buffed up with sow and invis then ported to Iceclad. Run to crystal caverns, and log at the zone. Then log in your main character and start pulling orcs to the zone. When a bottle of karsin acid (no drop) drops quickly log on the warrior to loot. Alternatively, if the queen is camped, get someone to invis your warrior and run him down to the queen room and ask to loot a sceptre of the coldain ancients (lore no drop) from her. Obviously, this is quite tricky, but I managed it first attempt with help from guildies camping the queen. </P><P>Next, run your warrior to thurgadin. Hand either the sceptre or acid to Erdaf Restil (both result in the same item: a gem of persuasion). Get someone to bind the warrior here and camp him here. Get your main character killing drakkal bllod wolves for a blood wolf harness. Once one drops, loot then have someone hand it to your warrior. </P><P>With the warrior again, get sowed and invised and run to kael. The wolf tamer is under the bridge near the tormax area. He won't respond to hails (he should con dubious) but will hand out items correctly. First give him the gem of persuasion, to recieve a giant's gem of persuasion. Then give him the blood wolf harness and the giants gem to recieve a giants control harness. Get translocated or run back to great divide. </P><P>The broodmother is unlikely to be up, she's on a 12hr spawn timer. Get someone to invis the warrior yet again and proceed with caution into the wurm caves. Log him out in the cave just past the guardian shardwurms (this is where the broodmother pops). </P><P>The final stage is a series of triggered events. When you see the broodmother's up, run your main character to the entrance of the coldain mines in which Korf Brokenhammer resides, and log out. Log the warrior back in and hand the broodmother the harness then IMMEDIATELY log the warrior back out and your main character back in. You have approximately 4 minutes before the broodmother reaches the mines. </P><P>With a reasonably fast PC, you should log in to see the 2 dwarves stood outside the cave with the broodmother still some way off. Target Korf and sit and wait (He will be approximately level 45 now). Eventually, the mother will arrive and attack, at which point you will lose your target. This is because korf depops then immediately repops with the bracer, and starts running. Retarget, then throw a quick snare at him (assuming you're a druid or ranger), and he'll attack you. The broodmother will be his pet and attack if you get too close to him, so root dotting or bow kiting is ideal. As a 54 druid, he took 2 rounds of breath or ro and winged death to kill, meaning he has around 5000hps... I've no idea what he hits for because i didn't get close enough to find out. Every snare and root I cast stuck fully, making things easy. When he dies, the broodmother should depop and you can walk over and loot the bracer. </P><P>Method 2 (non KOS) </P><P>This is similar but you save yourself the hassle of needing the alternate character. In CC, loot the acid or sceptre then hand in whilst invis in thurgadin (The quest intends for you to slip the acid in his drink, poisoning him and letting you steal the gem whilst he's distracted, although you can give him the sceptre and he hands the gem over willingly - no faction hits in either case). Kill a coldain war wolf in GD, and loot the war wolf choker. Hand the choker to the wolf trainer to get a drakkal blood wolf harness. Hand the gem in to get a giants gem of persuasion. Hand both these items in simultaneously to get your control harness. Give this to the broodmother to trigger the event, and follow the advice given in the previous section for killing korf. </P><P>A few facts... </P><P>If KOS to kael you CANNOT do this quest without using the warrior multiquest method above. You are GUARANTEED to be attacked in kael if you try handing in invis, and the items will in all probability be lost. </P><P>Korf is NOT 55 in the quest, as mentioned above he's nearer 45 with low MR and FR. He is however 55 when not in the quest, which obviously leads to some confusion. </P><P>You MUST wait for the broodmother to attack and repop korf before attacking him, if you attack prior to this you won't get the bracer. </P><P>You can depop the broodmother by killing whichever mob she's attached to as a pet... you don't need to kill the mother herself. She's a remarkably bugged mob and whilst will probably take Korf as a master she may pick a passing wolf or anything instead. It's common courtesy to depop her after you've done the quest if she doesn't automatically depop since if she's left wandering round following a wolf it's A) a nasty surprise for anyone that attacks the wolf and B) stops her respawning so others can do the quest.<BR></i></P><P>The dorf was light blue at 60, not very MR (resisted fear once, but the 2nd one went through for the entire length of the fight), hit 108ish if I remember right from looking at my other hits window and had quiet some hp for his level, nonetheless a walk in the park.<BR>Oh and don't attack him before he runs away, because if you do it before he won't drop the bracer.</P><P> </font></td>
      </tr>
      <TR>
        <TD bgcolor='black' valign='top'
 nowrap><b><font color='white' face='Verdana' size='2'>web_trader</font></b></td>
        <TD bgcolor='black' valign='top'><font color='white' face='Verdana' size='2'> I completed this quest last night.  I already had the blood wolf harness in the bank (was thinking of selling it in the Bazaar until I learned about this quest).  The total time for me was four hours.  It was very easy to do solo.</P><P>Too easy...</P><P>I suggest doing this quest ASAP because parts of it feel broken and are likely to get fixed (nerfed).  Or perhaps this really is Verant's gift to Necros?  Is there another level three focus item that is as easy to get solo as this item?  I don't know.</P><P>I am going to fill in some of the gaps in the walk through above while I still remember them.</P><P>I ran my level 1 Rallos Zek worshiping troll warior to Iceclad and bound him on the pier.  I then ran him carefully around the east edges of the islands and over the bridge to Eastern Wastes.  There are several mobs that can get in your way including dire wolves.  I suggest running around the western shor line which seems safer from my memory although it will take a little linger.</P><P>In EW, I noted that my troll was KOS to the orcs so I avoided their camp and ran right along the top of the cliffs until I got to the Coldain camp and camped out in one of the huts.  From memory, there are no mobs that will attack you at this Coldain camp.</P><P>I logged on my main level 55 necro and made my way to the Nexus.  I popped into Shadow Haven and purchased nine potions from the dorfs there.  I put the potions and the blood wolf harness in a ten slot backpack and ported down to Great Divide at the Velios spire in the Nexus.  I invised and ran to the coldain camp and dropped the backpack at the spot my troll was campled.  I logged out, logged the troll in and picked up the backpack.  This is a little bit risky because someone could come by and pick up the backpack.</P><P>I invised the troll and ran him to the orc fort.  My invis dropped once on the way so be carefull.  Got the troll into Crystal Caverns and camped.</P><P>I brought up the main again and proceeded to Crystal Caverns where I hunted orcs near the zone-in point until the acid dropped.  The karsin acid bottles are lore as well as no-drop.  I had hoped to get more than one of them for my troll in case I had to repeat any part of the quest.  It dropped very quickly for me on about the fifth kill.  I logged in the troll, picked up the acid, invised and ran to Great Divide.  Invis dropped again around the zone line but from zone into GD all the way to Kaladim, everything was dubious or apprehensive.  A kind stranger bound my troll in front of the bank in Kaladim.  This saved time later on.  To get to Erdaf Restil, with your back to the bank, turn right and go down the ramp.  Turn left into the tavern.  Erdaf is in there.  Give him the acid and he gets sick, drops the gem into your inventory and runs off.  I don't know what his respawn time is.</P><P>I ran the troll to Kael Drakal without invis.  If you hug the right wall on zone into Eastern Wastes, it should be pretty safe.  I conned all the giants in Kael and they were dubious all the way to the wolf taimer.  He is on the right below the transparent bridge to the King Tormax area.  On the left side of the bridge is a ramp so you will not need to jump down.  My Troll only had 35HP with his stamina maxed and I think he could die from any kind of fall.  I turned in the gem to get the giants gem.  I then turned in the giants gem and blood wolf harness to get the harness of control.  To save time, I just attacked the wolf traniner and my troll was back in Kaladim with all his items intact thanks to the new low level changes.</P><P>I ran the pet to the shard wurm caves which are due south along the glowing river in Great Divide.  I invised before I entered the caves.  I took the first tunnel on the left and turned left again into the guardian shardwurm cave.  At the back of that cave is another cave.  To my surprise, the brood mother was up when I got there.  I went all the way to the back of the cave behind the broodmother and camped, still invisable.</P><P>Back on my main, still in Crystal Caverns, I ran to the mine entrance in GD.  It is at approximately neg 6100 neg 3300 and looks like a large framed square opening on the side of a hill.  I medded to full and loaded up dot and DD spells.  I also memmed the level 49 pet spell.  One thing I forgot to do was to rebuff.  I suggest doing this.  I then camped.</P><P>I logged in the troll.  I was not able to hand in the harness of control to the broodmother invis.  I was able to determine the best place to stand since you still get the message "you are too far away to trade" while invis.  My invis dropped at that point and I was able to hand the harness of control to the broodmother without being attacked.  She wanders off at a slow pace.  I was able to return to the very back of the cave, sit and camp successfully without being attacked by any other wurms.</P><P>I logged my main back in and had plenty of time to prepare before the broodmother showed up.  I brought up the 49 pet, buffed it and was able med back to full.  I even had time to cast DMF on myself before she showed up.  The two dorfs were standing on either side of the mine entrance.  Korf is on the southern side.  The brood mother wandered in from the north and attacked the other dorf, not Korf.  Korf promptly respawned and ran to the south.  Happily the brood mother became the pet of the other dorf and I had Korf all to myself.  He runs pretty fast (not SOW) so I found it easiest to stop him by telling my pet to attack him.  I would have done the same even if the broodmother was his pet.  Every spell I tried stuck on him.  I went with cascading darkness, fear, VoS, splurt, fear, VoS and when fear ran off he was already trying to run away on his own.  I still had half my mana and I did not use lich.</P><P>As promised he dropped the bracer and I zoned back to my hunting spot one happy necro.  My only mistake was that I forgot to get my backback back from the troll before zoning out.</P><P>Sorry for being verbose but I like a lot of details before I try a quest like this solo.  It was far easier than I imagined it would be.  It would probably be a little harder if the broodmother winds up as Korfs pet.  Given the value of the prize and the ease of getting to the point where Korf respawns, it would not be too bad to repeat those steps if you cannot kill Korf for any reason.  If the broodmother is not up, you have quite a wait on your hands.  I suggest working on your CoV faction while waiting for her to spawn.  A level 50 necro should be able to do this quest, I think.</P><P> </font></td>
      </tr>
